viaideinfo: viaideinfo (Displays the information of installed VIA IDE controllers)
viaideinfo:
viaideinfo: This command-line application identifies VIA IDE controllers installed
viaideinfo: in the computer, and displays various information/statistics regarding
viaideinfo: these. This does not depend on the via82cxxx kernel IDE driver, and
viaideinfo: will work regardless of whether it is present or not. All this
viaideinfo: information used to be available through /proc/ide/via; however this
viaideinfo: file was removed in Linux 2.6.15 to reduce the complexity of the IDE
viaideinfo: driver. Since it performs some basic port I/O, it must be run as root.
viaideinfo: http://reactivated.net/software/viaideinfo
viaideinfo: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
